            <!-- for section 5: glossary of terms -->
            <div class='row'>
                <div class='col'>
                    <div class='card'>
                        <div class='card-header'>
                            <h2>Description List</h2>
                        </div>
                        <div class='card-body'>
                            <div class='card-tittle'>
                                <h3>CS400 terms</h3>
                            </div>
                            <dl>
                                <dt>Subset</dt>
                                <dd>A set A is a subset of another set B, if all members of A exist in B. Thus,
                                    a set is also a subset of itself while a proper subset is a subset that is
                                    not also equal to the original set. Example: The set of vowels (smaller
                                    circle) is a subset of the set of all letters (larger circle).</dd>
                                <dt>Superset</dt>
                                <dd>A set B is a superset of set A, if B contains all elements of A and
                                    additional elements that are not found in A. Example: The set of letters
                                    (larger circle) is a superset of the set of vowels (smaller circle).</dd>
                            </dl>
                        </div>
                    </div>
                </div>
            </div>
